1 Download alpine linux iso https://alpinelinux.org/downloads/
2 Flash iso
3 Enter to live environment
4 Login as root then run setup-alpine then setup alpine linux first
5 When on APK Mirror type c and f on disk & install How would you like to use it spenetration require crypt and sys
6 After install login then run doas apk add nano
7 If you are on GRUB run doas nano /etc/default/grub then change GRUB_TIMEOUT=2 to GRUB_TIMEOUT=5 Then change GRUB_DISABLE_RECOVERY=true to GRUB_DISABLE_RECOVERY=false
  Then remove quiet from GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="modules=sd-mod,usb-storage,ext4,bootpartition quiet rootfstype=ext4" to GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="modules=sd-mod,usb-storage,ext4,bootpartition rootfstype=ext4"
  Then add GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="Spenetration Linux"
  Then ctrl x y enter then doas grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
  
  If you are on syslinux run doas nano /boot/extlinux.conf
  Then Change MENU TITLE Alpine/Linux Boot Menu To Spenetration/Linux Boot Menu then on MENU AUTOBOOT Change Alpine will be booted automatically in # seconds. to Spenetration will be booted automatically in # seconds then on APPEND root Remove quiet
  Ctrl x y enter

8 Run doas nano /etc/os-release
  
  Then change The alpine linux to
  NAME="Spenetration Linux"
  ID=spenetration
  VERSION_ID=3.23.4
  PRETTY_NAME="Spenetration Linux v3.23"
  HOME_URL="https://github.com/syslacklinux/SPENETRATION-LINUX"
 
  
9 Run doas nano /etc/motd then change Welcome to Alpine!

The Alpine Wiki contains a large amount of how-to guides and general
information about administrating Alpine systems.
See <https://wiki.alpinelinux.org/>.

You can setup the system with the command: setup-alpine

You may change this message by editing /etc/motd.

To Welcome To Spenetration!

   The most advanced Penetration Testing Distribution
   Spenetration Linux is an open-source, Alpine-based Linux distribution geared towards various information security tasks, such as Penetration Testing, Security Research, Computer Forensics and Reverse Engineering.

